    {
        "content": "<p><code>deriv</code> eats a function and a value, however you only provided it a value</p>",
        "id": 515314731,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1746022051
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>deriv</code> takes function <code>f</code> and a value <code>x</code> as argument. So <code>deriv f x</code> means you are supplying <code>f</code> and <code>x</code> separately. In your first attempt, you are supplying an expression (i.e. a value) to <code>deriv</code></p>",
